Let's write the fixed version:

```java
private static String extractClassNameIfGoog(Node node, Node parent,
    String functionName){
  String className = null;
  if (NodeUtil.isExprCall(parent)) {
    Node callee = node.getFirstChild();
    if (callee != null && callee.getType() == Token.GETPROP) {
      String qualifiedName = callee.getQualifiedName();
      if (functionName.equals(qualifiedName)) {
        // The first argument is the file path, the second argument is the array of class names.
        Node firstArg = callee.getNext();
        if (firstArg != null) {
          Node secondArg = firstArg.getNext();
          if (secondArg != null && secondArg.getType() == Token.ARRAYLIT) {
            Node classNameNode = secondArg.getFirstChild();
            if (classNameNode != null && classNameNode.getType() == Token.STRING) {
              className = classNameNode.getString();
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return className;
}
```

This is a minimal fix: instead of getting the first argument's string, we get the second argument (which should be an array literal) and then get its first child (the class name string). This matches the typical usage in tests.

